, and exercise the command function. It has significant implications for both the development of military doctrine and the training and education of tomorrow's military leaders.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 12. Dez 2020) 0aCommand of troopsvCase studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Freedom.2bisacsh1 aMcmaster, H. R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477770440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804777704423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804777704.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles